text: The Orange Free State () was a country in southern Africa. It was ruled by the Afrikaners. It was defeated by the British Empire and its colonies, the British Cape Colony and the Natal Colony, in the Second Boer War. It became the Orange River Colony and later joined with other colonies to make the Union of South Africa. == References == Category:1852 establishments Category:19th- century establishments in South Africa Category:1900s disestablishments in Africa Category:1850s establishments in Africa Category:1900s disestablishments Category:Former countries in Africa
